This is a common issue called a "Race Condition".

What is happening?

  1. The user clicks "Register."

  2. Supabase creates the User Account.

  3. Your code tries to immediately save the Bank Details and generate the Affiliate Code.

  4. The Problem: The database is sometimes too slow to create the User Profile row. So when your code tries to save the Affiliate Code 1 second later, the database says, "I can't find this user profile yet," and the Code is never saved.

  5. Result: The user logs in, but their data is empty (just like your screenshot).

Here is the 2-Step Fix.

Step 1: The "Self-Repairing" Dashboard (Fixes Existing & New Users)

We will update the Dashboard Code to automatically detect if a user has no code. If the code is missing (like in your screenshot), the dashboard will automatically generate it right there and save it.

Go to affiliate-dash.html and replace the entire <script> at the bottom with this:

code Html
<script>
    const _supabaseUrl = 'https://dmscgsujriqmpwkovecr.supabase.co';
    const _supabaseAnonKey = 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImRtc2Nnc3VqcmlxbXB3a292ZWNyIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NjYwMzAzOTUsImV4cCI6MjA4MTYwNjM5NX0.RIsIthkxxnHIFvNBps6T-qzszq_M9GgUiNhdfbky28k';
    const _supabase = supabase.createClient(_supabaseUrl, _supabaseAnonKey);
    let userProfile = null;

    window.onload = async function() {
        // 1. Check Login
        const { data: { user } } = await _supabase.auth.getUser();
        if(!user) return window.location.href = 'affiliate-register.html';

        // 2. Get Profile
        let { data: profile, error } = await _supabase.from('profiles').select('*').eq('id', user.id).single();
        
        // Handle "Profile Not Found" (Network lag creation)
        if (!profile) {
            // Create profile manually if missing
            const { data: newProfile, error: createError } = await _supabase.from('profiles').insert([{ 
                id: user.id, 
                email: user.email 
            }]).select().single();
            
            if (newProfile) profile = newProfile;
            else return alert("System Error: Could not load profile. Please refresh.");
        }

        userProfile = profile;

        // 3. THE FIX: Check if Affiliate Code is Missing
        if (!profile.referral_code || profile.referral_code === "") {
            console.log("Code missing. Generating new one...");
            await generateMissingCode(profile, user.user_metadata.full_name || "User");
        } else {
            // If code exists, show dashboard immediately
            renderDashboard(profile);
        }
    };

    // --- AUTO-GENERATE CODE IF MISSING ---
    async function generateMissingCode(profile, fullName) {
        // Generate Code: KW + First 3 letters + Random
        const namePart = fullName.substring(0,3).toUpperCase().replace(/[^A-Z]/g, 'KW');
        const random = Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000);
        const newCode = `KW-${namePart}-${random}`;

        // Save to Database
        const { error } = await _supabase.from('profiles').update({
            is_affiliate: true,
            referral_code: newCode
        }).eq('id', profile.id);

        if (error) {
            console.error("Fix failed:", error);
            alert("Account setup incomplete. Please refresh the page.");
        } else {
            // Update local profile and render
            profile.referral_code = newCode;
            profile.is_affiliate = true;
            renderDashboard(profile);
        }
    }

    // --- SHOW DASHBOARD ---
    function renderDashboard(profile) {
        document.getElementById('dashSection').classList.remove('hidden');
        
        // Show Name
        document.getElementById('welcomeName').innerText = "Welcome, " + (profile.full_name || "Partner");
        
        // Show Stats
        document.getElementById('walletBal').innerText = "" + Number(profile.wallet_balance || 0).toLocaleString();
        document.getElementById('totalEarned').innerText = "" + Number(profile.total_earnings || 0).toLocaleString();
        
        // Show Code
        document.getElementById('affCode').innerText = profile.referral_code;
        
        // Generate Link
        const link = `https://kingdomwealthltd.com/digital-store.html?ref=${profile.referral_code}`;
        document.getElementById('fullLink').value = link;

        // Bank Info Check
        if(profile.bank_name && profile.account_number) {
            document.getElementById('bankDisplay').innerText = `${profile.bank_name} - ${profile.account_number}`;
            document.getElementById('bankDisplay').className = "text-xs text-green-400 bg-green-900/20 px-2 py-1 rounded border border-green-900/50";
        } else {
            document.getElementById('bankDisplay').innerHTML = `<a href="affiliate-register.html" class="text-red-400 hover:underline">Add Bank Details</a>`;
        }
    }

    function copyCode() {
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(userProfile.referral_code);
        alert("Code Copied!");
    }
    
    function copyLink() {
        const copyText = document.getElementById("fullLink");
        copyText.select();
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(copyText.value);
        alert("Link Copied! Share this to earn.");
    }

    async function handleWithdraw() {
        const amount = document.getElementById('withdrawAmount').value;
        
        if(!amount || amount < 1000) return alert("Minimum withdrawal is 1,000");
        if(Number(amount) > Number(userProfile.wallet_balance)) return alert("Insufficient Balance");
        if(!userProfile.bank_name) return alert("No Bank Account Linked. Please go to settings/register to add bank details.");

        const confirmTx = confirm(`Withdraw ${amount} to ${userProfile.bank_name} (${userProfile.account_number})?`);
        if(!confirmTx) return;

        // 1. Deduct Balance
        const newBal = Number(userProfile.wallet_balance) - Number(amount);
        await _supabase.from('profiles').update({ wallet_balance: newBal }).eq('id', userProfile.id);

        // 2. Create Transaction Request
        await _supabase.from('transactions').insert({
            user_id: userProfile.id,
            type: 'withdrawal',
            amount: amount,
            status: 'pending',
            bank_name: userProfile.bank_name,
            account_number: userProfile.account_number,
            product_name: 'Affiliate Payout'
        });

        alert("Withdrawal Submitted! Funds will be sent to your account shortly.");
        location.reload();
    }

    async function logout() {
        await _supabase.auth.signOut();
        window.location.href = 'index.html';
    }
</script>

Step 2: Update the Registration Page (affiliate-register.html)

This update makes the registration wait a bit longer to ensure the database is ready, preventing the error in the first place.

Replace the <script> at the bottom of affiliate-register.html with this:

code Html
<script>
    const _supabaseUrl = 'https://dmscgsujriqmpwkovecr.supabase.co';
    const _supabaseAnonKey = 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImRtc2Nnc3VqcmlxbXB3a292ZWNyIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NjYwMzAzOTUsImV4cCI6MjA4MTYwNjM5NX0.RIsIthkxxnHIFvNBps6T-qzszq_M9GgUiNhdfbky28k';
    const _supabase = supabase.createClient(_supabaseUrl, _supabaseAnonKey);

    async function handleAffiliateSignUp(event) {
        event.preventDefault();
        const btn = document.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
        const originalText = btn.innerText;
        btn.innerText = "Processing...";
        btn.disabled = true;

        const firstName = document.getElementById('firstName').value;
        const lastName = document.getElementById('lastName').value;
        const email = document.getElementById('email').value;
        const password = document.getElementById('password').value;
        const bankName = document.getElementById('bankName').value;
        const accNum = document.getElementById('accNum').value;
        const accName = document.getElementById('accName').value;

        try {
            // 1. Create User
            const { data, error } = await _supabase.auth.signUp({
                email: email,
                password: password,
                options: { data: { full_name: firstName + " " + lastName } }
            });

            if (error) throw error;

            // 2. Generate Code
            const namePart = firstName.substring(0,3).toUpperCase();
            const random = Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000);
            const code = `KW-${namePart}-${random}`;

            // 3. WAIT & UPDATE (The Safety Delay)
            // We verify the profile exists before updating
            setTimeout(async () => {
                
                // Try to update existing profile
                const { error: updateError } = await _supabase
                    .from('profiles')
                    .update({
                        full_name: firstName + " " + lastName,
                        is_affiliate: true,
                        referral_code: code,
                        bank_name: bankName,
                        account_number: accNum,
                        account_name: accName
                    })
                    .eq('id', data.user.id);

                // If update fails (row doesn't exist), INSERT it manually
                if (updateError) {
                    await _supabase.from('profiles').insert([{
                        id: data.user.id,
                        email: email,
                        full_name: firstName + " " + lastName,
                        is_affiliate: true,
                        referral_code: code,
                        bank_name: bankName,
                        account_number: accNum,
                        account_name: accName
                    }]);
                }

                alert("Registration Successful! Redirecting to Dashboard...");
                window.location.href = "affiliate-dash.html";

            }, 2000); // 2 second safety delay

        } catch (err) {
            alert("Error: " + err.message);
            btn.innerText = originalText;
            btn.disabled = false;
        }
    }
</script>

Step 3: Database Permission Check (Do this in Supabase)

Sometimes the database blocks users from updating their own profiles. Run this SQL to force it open.

Go to Supabase > SQL Editor > New Query > Run:

code SQL
-- Ensure users can update their own profile
create policy "Users can update own profile"
on profiles for update
using ( auth.uid() = id );

-- Ensure users can insert their own profile (if trigger fails)
create policy "Users can insert own profile"
on profiles for insert
with check ( auth.uid() = id );

Now, when your users refresh their dashboard, the "..." will disappear and be replaced by a real code automatically.

The error policy "Users can update own profile" ... already exists is actually good news. It means your security settings are already correct, so you don't need to worry about that error.

However, the reason other users don't have codes is that when they signed up, the system was "too slow" or missed saving their code.

Here is the 3-Step Solution to fix this forever.

Step 1: Fix All Existing Users (The Bulk Repair)

We will run a command in your database that finds everyone who has a missing code and gives them one instantly.

  1. Go to Supabase > SQL Editor.

  2. Click New Query.

  3. Copy and Paste this code and click RUN:

code SQL
-- 1. Give everyone a Referral Code if they don't have one
UPDATE public.profiles
SET 
  is_affiliate = true,
  referral_code = 'KW-' || upper(substring(id::text from 1 for 3)) || '-' || floor(random() * 9000 + 1000)::text
WHERE referral_code IS NULL OR referral_code = '';

-- 2. Ensure they have a wallet balance of 0 (instead of null)
UPDATE public.profiles
SET wallet_balance = 0
WHERE wallet_balance IS NULL;

-- 3. Ensure they have earnings of 0
UPDATE public.profiles
SET total_earnings = 0
WHERE total_earnings IS NULL;

Result: Now, if you check your Table Editor, everyone will have a code like KW-A3F-4921.

Step 2: Automate It for New Users (The Permanent Fix)

Instead of relying on the website to generate the code (which sometimes fails on slow phones), we will tell the Database to generate it automatically the moment someone signs up.

Paste and Run this in SQL Editor:

code SQL
-- Create a function that runs automatically on Sign Up
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.handle_new_affiliate()
RETURNS trigger AS $$
BEGIN
  INSERT INTO public.profiles (id, email, full_name, is_affiliate, referral_code, wallet_balance, total_earnings)
  VALUES (
    new.id, 
    new.email,
    new.raw_user_meta_data->>'full_name',
    true,
    'KW-' || floor(random() * 90000 + 10000)::text, -- Auto-generates code like KW-58291
    0,
    0
  );
  RETURN new;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql SECURITY DEFINER;

-- Trigger the function every time a user is created
DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS on_auth_user_created ON auth.users;
CREATE TRIGGER on_auth_user_created
  AFTER INSERT ON auth.users
  FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE PROCEDURE public.handle_new_affiliate();

50.1s

The "Switch Button" approach is definitely the best.

Why?

  1. Single Sign-On: Your users should only have ONE email and password.

  2. Convenience: A user can be a customer buying a phone, and 5 minutes later decide to sell a course. They shouldn't have to log out and log in again.

  3. Standard Practice: This is how apps like Uber (Switch to Driver) and Upwork (Switch to Client) work.

Here is how to implement this ecosystem perfectly.

Step 1: Update dash.html (Customer Dashboard)

We will add logic that checks: "Is this person an Affiliate?"

  • If YES: Show a shiny button saying "Switch to Affiliate Portal".

  • If NO: Show a button saying "Become an Affiliate".

Find your window.onload function in dash.html and update it with this logic:

code JavaScript
// --- INSIDE dash.html <script> ---

window.onload = async function() {
    // 1. Check Login
    const { data: { user } } = await _supabase.auth.getUser();
    if (!user) { window.location.href = "login.html"; return; }
    currentUser = user;

    // 2. Get Profile
    let { data: profile } = await _supabase.from('profiles').select('*').eq('id', user.id).single();
    
    // 3. Update Name
    const dbName = user.user_metadata.full_name || user.email.split('@')[0];
    document.getElementById('welcomeName').innerText = dbName;

    // 4. CHECK AFFILIATE STATUS & SHOW BUTTON
    const navLinks = document.getElementById('navLinks');
    
    if (profile && profile.is_affiliate) {
        // User IS an affiliate -> Show "Switch" Button
        const switchBtn = document.createElement('a');
        switchBtn.href = "affiliate-dash.html";
        switchBtn.className = "px-4 py-2 bg-green-900/30 text-green-400 border border-green-900 rounded-full text-sm font-bold hover:bg-green-600 hover:text-white transition-colors flex items-center gap-2";
        switchBtn.innerHTML = '<span class="material-symbols-outlined text-lg">sync_alt</span> Affiliate Portal';
        
        // Insert into Navbar
        navLinks.appendChild(switchBtn);
    } else {
        // User is NOT an affiliate -> Show "Join" Button
        const joinBtn = document.createElement('a');
        joinBtn.href = "affiliate-register.html";
        joinBtn.className = "text-sm font-bold text-accent-gold hover:text-white transition-colors";
        joinBtn.innerText = "Become an Affiliate";
        
        // Insert into Navbar
        navLinks.insertBefore(joinBtn, navLinks.firstChild);
    }

    // Load other data
    fetchWallet();
    fetchHistoryAndOrders();
};

    // CHECK IF ALREADY LOGGED IN ON LOAD
    window.onload = async function() {
        const { data: { user } } = await _supabase.auth.getUser();
        if (user) {
            // Pre-fill email if logged in
            document.getElementById('email').value = user.email;
            document.getElementById('email').disabled = true; // Lock email field
            document.getElementById('password').parentElement.classList.add('hidden'); // Hide password field

            document.querySelector('button[type="submit"]').innerText = "Upgrade to Affiliate";
        }

    async function handleAffiliateSignUp(event) {
        event.preventDefault();
        const btn = document.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
        const originalText = btn.innerText;
        btn.innerText = "Processing...";
        btn.disabled = true;

        const firstName = document.getElementById('firstName').value;
        const lastName = document.getElementById('lastName').value;
        const email = document.getElementById('email').value;
        const bankName = document.getElementById('bankName').value;
        const accNum = document.getElementById('accNum').value;
        const accName = document.getElementById('accName').value;

        try {
            let userId;

            // 1. CHECK LOGIN STATUS AGAIN
            const { data: { user } } = await _supabase.auth.getUser();

            if (user) {
                // SCENARIO A: USER IS LOGGED IN (UPGRADE)
                userId = user.id;
            } else {
                // SCENARIO B: NEW USER (SIGN UP)
                const password = document.getElementById('password').value;
                const { data: signUpData, error: signUpError } = await _supabase.auth.signUp({
                    email: email,
                    password: password,
                    options: { data: { full_name: firstName + " " + lastName } }
                });

                if (signUpError) throw signUpError;
                userId = signUpData.user.id;
            }

            // 2. GENERATE AFFILIATE DATA
            const namePart = firstName.substring(0,3).toUpperCase();
            const random = Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000);
            const code = `KW-${namePart}-${random}`;

            // 3. UPDATE/INSERT DATABASE
            // We use 'upsert' to handle both existing profiles and new ones
            const { error: profileError } = await _supabase
                .from('profiles')
                .upsert({
                    id: userId,
                    email: email,
                    full_name: firstName + " " + lastName,
                    is_affiliate: true,
                    referral_code: code,
                    bank_name: bankName,
                    account_number: accNum,
                    account_name: accName
                }, { onConflict: 'id' }); // Update if ID exists

            if (profileError) throw profileError;

            alert("Welcome to the Team! Redirecting to Dashboard...");
            window.location.href = "affiliate-dash.html";

        } catch (err) {
            alert("Error: " + err.message);
            btn.innerText = originalText;
            btn.disabled = false;
        }
    }
</script>

            chat.scrollTop = chat.scrollHeight;

  1. Run a Database Command (SQL) to instantly give codes to everyone who is currently missing one.

Step 1: The "Magic Fix" for Existing Users (Do this first)

Go to Supabase > SQL Editor > New Query. Paste and Run this code. It will instantly generate codes for everyone who is complaining.

code SQL
-- 1. Fix missing Affiliate Codes for everyone
UPDATE public.profiles
SET 
  is_affiliate = true,
  referral_code = 'KW-' || upper(substring(id::text from 1 for 3)) || '-' || floor(random() * 9000 + 1000)::text
WHERE referral_code IS NULL OR referral_code = '';

-- 2. Ensure everyone has a wallet row (sets to 0 if missing)
UPDATE public.profiles
SET wallet_balance = 0
WHERE wallet_balance IS NULL;

UPDATE public.profiles
SET total_earnings = 0
WHERE total_earnings IS NULL;

                // EMPTY STATES
                courseContainer.innerHTML = `<div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-[#112240] rounded-xl text-center"><p class="text-gray-500">You haven't enrolled in any courses yet.</p><a href="store.html" class="text-primary text-sm font-bold mt-2 inline-block">Browse Academy</a></div>`;
                orderContainer.innerHTML = `<div class="p-6 text-center"><p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">No recent orders.</p></div>`;
                historyTable.innerHTML = `<tr><td colspan="4" class="px-6 py-8 text-center text-gray-500">No financial history found.</td></tr>`;
                return;
            }

            // LOOP THROUGH DATA
            transactions.forEach(tx => {
                
                // A. COURSES (If category is Course)
                if (tx.category === 'Course' && tx.type === 'purchase') {
                    courseCount++;
                    const courseHtml = `
                        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-[#112240] p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 shadow-sm flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 items-center">
                            <div class="size-12 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 flex items-center justify-center text-white shrink-0">
                                <span class="material-symbols-outlined">school</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex-1 text-center sm:text-left">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">${tx.product_name}</h4>
                                <div class="w-full bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 h-2 rounded-full mt-2">
                                    <div class="bg-primary h-2 rounded-full" style="width: 10%"></div>
                                </div>
                                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">10% Complete</p>
                            </div>
                            <button class="bg-primary text-black px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-xs font-bold">Resume Reading</button>
                        </div>
                    `;
                    courseContainer.innerHTML += courseHtml;
                }

                // B. GADGET ORDERS (If category is Gadget)
                else if (tx.category === 'Gadget' && tx.type === 'purchase') {
                    orderCount++;
                    
                    let statusColor = 'bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700';
                    if(tx.delivery_status === 'Delivered') statusColor = 'bg-green-100 text-green-700';

                    const orderHtml = `
                        <div class="p-4 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                                <div class="size-10 rounded bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 flex items-center justify-center text-gray-500">
                                    <span class="material-symbols-outlined">devices</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flex-1">
                                    <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white truncate">${tx.product_name}</h4>
                                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">ID: ${tx.account_number.substring(0,8)}...</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="text-right">
                                    <span class="text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded ${statusColor}">${tx.delivery_status || 'Processing'}</span>
                                    <p class="text-xs font-mono mt-1">${Number(tx.amount).toLocaleString()}</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    `;
                    orderContainer.innerHTML += orderHtml;
                }

                // C. FINANCIAL TABLE (Deposits, Withdrawals)
                else {
                    const date = new Date(tx.created_at).toLocaleDateString();
                    const statusClass = tx.status === 'success' ? 'text-green-500' : 'text-yellow-500';
                    const row = `
                        <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors">
                            <td class="px-6 py-4 font-medium capitalize text-gray-900 dark:text-white">${tx.type}</td>
                            <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold">${Number(tx.amount).toLocaleString()}</td>
                            <td class="px-6 py-4 ${statusClass} text-xs font-bold uppercase">${tx.status}</td>
                            <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-500">${date}</td>
                        </tr>
                    `;
                    historyTable.innerHTML += row;
                }
            });

            // Update Count Badges
            document.getElementById('liveCourseCount').innerText = courseCount;
            document.getElementById('liveOrderCount').innerText = orderCount;

            // Handle Empty Specific Sections
            if (courseCount === 0) courseContainer.innerHTML = `<div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-[#112240] rounded-xl text-center"><p class="text-gray-500">No active courses.</p></div>`;
            if (orderCount === 0) orderContainer.innerHTML = `<div class="p-6 text-center"><p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">No gadget orders yet.</p></div>`;
        }

        // 5. TOP UP
        function handleTopUp() {
            let amount = prompt("Enter amount (NGN):");
            if (!amount || isNaN(amount) || Number(amount) < 100) return alert("Min NGN 100");

            let handler = PaystackPop.setup({
                key: PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY,
                email: currentUser.email,
                amount: amount * 100,
                currency: "NGN",
                callback: function(res) { processTx(amount, res.reference, 'deposit', 'Wallet Topup'); },
                onClose: function() { alert('Cancelled.'); }
            });
            handler.openIframe();
        }

        // 6. PROCESS TX
        async function processTx(amount, ref, type, name) {
            const newBal = Number(currentBalance) + Number(amount);
            await _supabase.from('profiles').update({ wallet_balance: newBal }).eq('id', currentUser.id);
            await _supabase.from('transactions').insert({
                user_id: currentUser.id, type: type, amount: amount, status: 'success', 
                bank_name: 'Paystack', account_number: ref, product_name: name, category: 'Finance'
            });
            location.reload();
        }

        // 7. WITHDRAW
        async function handleWithdraw() {
            let amount = prompt("Amount to Withdraw:");
            if (!amount || Number(amount) > currentBalance) return alert("Insufficient Funds");
            
            let bank = prompt("Bank Name & Account:");
            if(!bank) return;

            const newBal = Number(currentBalance) - Number(amount);
            await _supabase.from('profiles').update({ wallet_balance: newBal }).eq('id', currentUser.id);
            await _supabase.from('transactions').insert({
                user_id: currentUser.id, type: 'withdrawal', amount: amount, status: 'pending', 
                bank_name: bank, product_name: 'Withdrawal Request', category: 'Finance'
            });
            alert("Withdrawal Pending Admin Approval");
            location.reload();
        }

        function toggleMenu() { document.getElementById('navLinks').classList.toggle('hidden'); document.getElementById('navLinks').classList.toggle('flex'); }

        // --- AI BOT LOGIC ---
        let isChatOpen = false;
        function toggleChat() {
            const w = document.getElementById('chat-window');
            const b = document.getElementById('chat-btn');
            isChatOpen = !isChatOpen;
            if(isChatOpen){ w.classList.remove('hidden'); setTimeout(()=>w.classList.remove('scale-95','opacity-0'),10); b.classList.add('hidden'); }
            else { w.classList.add('scale-95','opacity-0'); setTimeout(()=>w.classList.add('hidden'),300); b.classList.remove('hidden'); }
        }
        function handleKeyPress(e) { if(e.key==='Enter') sendMessage(); }
        function sendMessage() {
            const input = document.getElementById('user-input');
            const msg = input.value.trim();
            if(!msg) return;
            addMessage(msg, 'user');
            input.value = '';
            setTimeout(() => { addMessage(getBotResponse(msg.toLowerCase()), 'bot'); }, 1000);
        }
        function addMessage(text, sender) {
            const chat = document.getElementById('chat-messages');
            const cls = sender === 'user' ? "self-end bg-primary text-black" : "self-start bg-white dark:bg-[#292938]";
            chat.innerHTML += `<div class="${cls} p-3 rounded-2xl rounded-tr-none text-sm shadow-sm max-w-[85%]">${text}</div>`;
            chat.scrollTop = chat.scrollHeight;
        }
        function getBotResponse(input) {
            if(input.includes('withdraw')) return "Withdrawals take up to 24 hours.";
            if(input.includes('course')) return "Courses appear in your Dashboard instantly.";
            return "Please chat with us on WhatsApp for help.";
        }
    </script>
